# git init 
the git init  command is use to create an empty repository.
if you wanted to create a new directory and initialize a git init repository , you can do so the following 
mkidir NewDirectory 
cd Newdirectory 
git init
once inside a  git repository , you can start using commands such as
[status](./status.md),
[add](./add.md),
[commit](./commit.md),
[push](./puch.md)
and more.
init will create the repository in the current diroctory and will encapsulate all content, including other directories
